-- Flyway baseline V1 for Musicode H2 database.
--
-- Derived from a live `SCRIPT TO` dump of data/musicode-db.mv.db taken on
-- 2026-04-16 (H2 2.3.232). See decision D024: the baseline is the real
-- on-disk schema, never a reconstruction from JPA entities. This preserves
-- the exact H2-generated constraint/index names that already live in the
-- production DB so `baseline-on-migrate=true` does not drift.
--
-- Sanitization applied to the raw dump:
--   * removed the `CREATE USER "SA" ...` line (user exists already, and
--     the password hash is environment-specific)
--   * removed `SET DB_CLOSE_DELAY -1` (that is set via JDBC URL)
--   * removed all `INSERT` statements and `-- N +/- SELECT COUNT(*)` comments
--     (this is a schema baseline, not a data snapshot)
--   * changed `CREATE CACHED TABLE` to `CREATE TABLE` (CACHED is an H2 hint;
--     CREATE TABLE is already cached by default in H2 2.x)
--   * stripped `NOCHECK` from foreign keys (NOCHECK is a restore-time flag
--     used by SCRIPT to skip validation on reload; real migrations validate)

