# Decisions Register

<!-- Append-only. Never edit or remove existing rows.
     To reverse a decision, add a new row that supersedes it.
     Read this file at the start of any planning or research phase. -->

| # | When | Scope | Decision | Choice | Rationale | Revisable? | Made By |
|---|------|-------|----------|--------|-----------|------------|---------|
| D001 |  | architecture | Audio playback mechanism | HTML5 Audio element with HTTP Range streaming (206 Partial Content) | FLAC is natively supported in Chrome, Edge, and Firefox. No transcoding needed for desktop use. Range headers enable seeking in large files (30-80MB FLACs) without full download. | Yes | human |
| D002 |  | architecture | Frontend framework and tooling | React 19 + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + TanStack Query | Modern, fast dev experience. Vite for instant HMR. TypeScript for type safety. Tailwind for rapid styling. TanStack Query for server state management with caching and pagination. User's preferred stack per PLAN.md. | Yes | human |
| D004 |  | architecture | Backend framework and runtime | Spring Boot 3 + Java 21 + Gradle (Kotlin DSL) | User's habitual stack. Modern Java features, virtual threads potential, native compilation path. Gradle Kotlin DSL for type-safe build config. | Yes | human |
| D005 |  | architecture | Database choice | H2 in file mode (embedded) | Zero config, ships as JAR dependency, no external server. Sufficient for single-user personal media library. | Yes | human |
| D006 |  | architecture | Audio metadata reading library | JAudioTagger 2.2.5 | Pure Java, supports ID3/Vorbis/MP4 tags and embedded cover art under a unified API. 3.x not available in Maven Central; 2.2.5 covers all needed formats. | Yes | human |
| D007 |  | architecture | Audio playback and streaming mechanism | HTML5 Audio element + HTTP Range headers (206 Partial Content) | FLAC natively supported in Chrome/Edge/Firefox. Range headers enable seeking in large files without full download. No transcoding needed for desktop. | Yes | human |
| D008 |  | architecture | Backend build tool | Maven (supersedes D004 which said Gradle) | Maven es el stack habitual del usuario. En un proyecto donde el frontend ya es aprendizaje nuevo (React), mantener el backend en terreno conocido reduce la carga cognitiva. Gradle Kotlin DSL tiene curva de aprendizaje innecesaria aquí. | Yes | human |
| D009 |  | architecture | Audio format support scope for MVP | Solo FLAC en MVP, multi-formato diferido | Reducir alcance del MVP a un solo formato simplifica el desarrollo. FLAC es lossless y el caso de uso principal del usuario. MP3/OGG/M4A se añaden después del MVP. | Yes | human |
| D010 |  | architecture | Target operating system | Windows 11 como entorno de desarrollo y ejecución principal | El usuario desarrolla y usará Musicode en Windows 11. Afecta rutas de filesystem (backslash, letras de unidad), volume mounts en Docker Desktop (WSL2), y testing. El backend debe usar java.nio.file.Path para abstracción de rutas cross-platform. | Yes | human |
| D011 |  | design | UI theme direction | Keep current dark theme (zinc + indigo accents). No light mode. Custom themes deferred to future milestone. | User likes the current dark palette (zinc grays + indigo blues). Light mode not needed. Custom themes are a future possibility but not priority. | Yes | human |
| D012 |  | quality | Minimum test coverage threshold for the project | 80% line coverage enforced via JaCoCo (backend) and @vitest/coverage-v8 (frontend). Builds fail if coverage drops below threshold. | Ensures all new code ships with meaningful test coverage. 80% is pragmatic — catches gaps without forcing pointless tests on trivial code. | Yes | human |
| D013 |  | architecture | Database engine for project | Stay with H2 — no migration needed currently | H2 is giving zero problems. SQLite is natural next step if needed. PostgreSQL only if full-text search or complex analytics (listening stats) are required in the future. | Yes — revisit if H2 hits limitations or advanced features are needed | collaborative |
| D014 |  | roadmap | Redis integration | Deferred — token blacklist + rate limiting + session cache in future milestone | M003 uses H2 table for refresh tokens. Redis milestone will compare approaches and teach Spring Data Redis, TTL, pub/sub for invalidation. | Yes | collaborative |
| D015 | M003/S02 | security | CSRF protection strategy for cookie-based JWT auth | CSRF disabled, rely on SameSite=Strict cookies | SameSite=Strict prevents the browser from sending cookies on cross-origin requests, which is the primary CSRF vector. Our SPA is same-origin. If we ever relax to SameSite=Lax (for external links), we'll need to add CookieCsrfTokenRepository. | Yes — revisit if SameSite is relaxed to Lax | agent |
| D016 |  | architecture | DTOs as Records vs Lombok classes | Migrate DTOs to Java Records in cleanup task post-M003 | Java 21 Records are idiomatic for immutable data carriers. All current DTOs qualify. JPA entities stay with Lombok. Deferred to avoid churn mid-milestone. | No | collaborative |
| D017 |  | roadmap | Post-M006 milestone sequence and feature grouping | M007 Listening Intelligence → M008 Audio Experience → M009 Smart Library → M010 Visual Experience → M011 Integrations & Streaming | M007 first: redondest milestone (backend + frontend + external API), each slice delivers visible value. M008 second: touches the core player, defines identity as an audiophile tool. M009-M011 follow by decreasing priority — smart library management, then visual polish, then external integrations. Letras (.lrc) considered for M008 but kept in M011 to avoid scope creep on the audio pipeline milestone. | Yes — features can move between milestones during planning | collaborative |
| D018 |  | architecture | API documentation tooling | SpringDoc OpenAPI 2.8.14 with springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui | Auto-generated from controller annotations, Swagger UI for interactive testing, OpenAPI 3.0 spec reusable. Chosen over Bruno (manual maintenance). Pinned to 2.8.14 — 2.8.15+ incompatible with Spring Boot 3.4.4. | Yes | collaborative |
| D019 |  | quality | E2E testing framework | Playwright with Chromium, sequential single-worker, HTML reporter | Real browser testing covers integration gaps unit tests miss. Sequential + single worker avoids H2 race conditions. Vite dev server auto-started via webServer config. Backend must be pre-started manually. | Yes | collaborative |
| D020 |  | architecture | Scrobbling integration architecture | Per-user scrobbling via Last.fm session key + ListenBrainz token, async fire-and-forget from PlayController | Two-level credentials: app-level API key for Last.fm (env vars), user-level tokens stored in User entity. Async with retry — never blocks playback. Last.fm mobile auth flow gives permanent session key. ListenBrainz uses simple bearer token. Both optional, configured per user in Settings. | Yes | collaborative |
| D021 |  | architecture | Album grouping strategy during library scan | ALBUM_ARTIST tag for album grouping, fallback to track ARTIST | Prevents compilation albums from fragmenting into N entries when each track has a different artist. ALBUM_ARTIST is the ID3/Vorbis standard for this purpose. Compilations without ALBUM_ARTIST still fragment — fixable via future metadata editing feature. | Yes | agent |
| D022 |  | library | Charting library for stats dashboard | Recharts for stats charts in the frontend | Recharts is React-native, composable, well-maintained, and matches the project's dark theme with custom styling. Simpler than D3 for the bar/line charts needed. Only used in StatsPage. | Yes | agent |
| D023 |  | roadmap | Pause new features and consolidate existing codebase first | Consolidation milestone (M008) before new features. Address test gaps, verify scrobbling, add Flyway, lazy routes, and frontend structure. | 7 milestones of feature work accumulated tech debt: untested services, unverified external integrations, no DB migrations, growing frontend without structure. Shipping more features on a shaky foundation multiplies future cost. Original M008 (Audio Experience) renumbered to M009+. | Yes | collaborative |
| D024 | M008/S03 | architecture | Flyway baseline strategy for existing H2 database | Export real H2 schema via SCRIPT TO before creating V1__baseline.sql — never reconstruct from JPA entities | ddl-auto:update generates schema incrementally over 7 milestones. The actual H2 schema may differ from what JPA entities would generate fresh (column ordering, constraint names, index quirks). Using the real schema dump as V1 prevents subtle mismatches that cause Flyway validation failures. | Yes | human |
| D025 | M009 discussion | roadmap | Split original M009 Audio Experience into two milestones | M009: Audio Pipeline & Gapless (foundational graph + gapless) → M010: Audio Experience (crossfade, EQ, enhanced visualizer). Supersedes D017 milestone sequence. | Pipeline migration and gapless are architecturally foundational — they change how audio flows. If they fail, everything built on top (crossfade, EQ, visualizer) collapses. Better to validate the base as a closed milestone before extending it. Remaining milestones shift: M010→M011 Smart Library, M011→M012 Visual Experience, M012→M013 Integrations. | No | collaborative |
| D026 | M009 discussion | architecture | Audio graph architecture | Centralized audioGraph.ts module encapsulating the full Web Audio API graph: source → GainNode → [insert chain] → AnalyserNode → destination. Hooks consume this module instead of managing their own singletons. | Current code has dispersed singletons (globalAudio in usePlayer.ts, audioContext/analyserNode in useAudioAnalyser.ts) that don't coordinate. A single module gives one point for inserting/removing nodes (EQ, crossfade, effects). Extending the current separation would require coordinating between unrelated modules. | No | collaborative |
| D027 | M009 discussion | architecture | Gapless playback implementation strategy | Dual HTMLAudioElement with precise swap — two audio elements, each with its own createMediaElementSource connected to the graph. Pre-load next track on second element, swap at track end. | Simpler than buffer puente (partial fetch + decodeAudioData). No memory problem with large FLACs (30-80MB → 200-500MB decoded in RAM). Near-gapless timing (~0-50ms) sufficient for personal use. Alternative: full AudioBuffer decode is impractical at ~101MB per 5-minute stereo 44.1kHz track. | Yes — if near-gapless proves insufficient for live albums | collaborative |
| D028 | M009 discussion | architecture | Audio preferences storage | localStorage for all audio preferences (volume, shuffle, repeat, future EQ/crossfade settings) | Device-local, simple, no backend changes needed. For a personal project, cross-device sync is not required. If needed later, migrate to User entity backend persistence. | Yes — if cross-device sync becomes desired | collaborative |
| D029 | M009 discussion | design | Audio feature defaults philosophy | Gapless always on. Crossfade opt-in (slider 0-12s, default 0/off). EQ opt-in (default flat/off). Visualizer modes selectable (current bars as default). | Philosophy: "tu audio suena exactamente como antes hasta que tú decidas cambiarlo." Gapless is objectively better with no downside. Crossfade and EQ are subjective preferences — activating them by default alters audio without consent, which is anti-audiophile. | No | collaborative |
| D030 | M010 discussion | architecture | EQ band count and frequencies | 5-band parametric EQ: 60Hz (lowshelf), 230Hz (peaking), 910Hz (peaking), 3.6kHz (peaking), 14kHz (highshelf). BiquadFilterNode instances in series. | 5 bands give sufficient control without overloading the UI. Logarithmic distribution covers the audible spectrum evenly. 3 bands too basic, 10 bands excessive for personal use. Standard distribution used by many consumer EQs. | Yes — band count can be adjusted | collaborative |
